Understanding your strengths: last week I had the chance to reconnect with an old friend and training partner down in Austin :) Chris Weidman is of course a UFC legend and had a very impressive career as an All-American college wrestler prior to his life in MMA. Some of the many things that have made him so spectacular over the years are his technical acumen, his speed and power, and his ability to adapt his wrestling to jiu-jitsu and mma. When someone is such an extraordinary athlete, it's easy to attribute their success to their ability to deploy attributes that the rest of us just don't have. While this can certainly help lead them to the highest levels, it’s important not to overlook something important: just as top-level athletes know how to leverage their best assets for maximum results, you too can leverage YOUR OWN strengths to help you maximize your results. You don't want to rely exclusively on your attributes... but if you use your strengths to strengthen your weaknesses, you'll have a chance to develop the strongest jiu-jitsu you possibly can. Great to see you again Chris!
